# Frontend Rules — Next.js 14 App Router

## Architecture
- App Router only — no Pages Router
- Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Data fetching in Server Components via `fetch()` with `cache` and `revalidate` options
- Mutations via Server Actions — no separate API route for simple form submissions
- Route handlers (`route.ts`) for: webhook receivers, streaming endpoints, WebSocket upgrades

## Data fetching patterns

### Server Component (preferred for static/revalidated data)
```tsx
// app/dashboard/page.tsx
import { getCubeMetrics } from "@/lib/cube"

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const metrics = await getCubeMetrics({ range: "7d" }) // fetched server-side
  return <MetricsGrid metrics={metrics} />
}
```

### Client Component with SWR (for live-updating data)
```tsx
"use client"
import useSWR from "swr"

export function LiveCampaignTable() {
  const { data, error, isLoading } = useSWR("/api/campaigns", fetcher, {
    refreshInterval: 60_000, // refresh every 60s
  })
  // ...
}
```

### Streaming / WebSocket (for insight feed)
```tsx
"use client"
import { useInsightStream } from "@/hooks/use-insight-stream"

export function InsightFeed() {
  const { insights, status } = useInsightStream() // connects to /api/insights/stream
  // ...
}
```

