```

## Component rules
- One component per file
- Server Components: no hooks, no event handlers, no browser APIs
- Client Components: keep them as small as possible — hoist data fetching to server
- Never import server-only modules (`db`, `redis`) in Client Components
- Use `next/image` for all images — never raw `<img>` tags
- Use `next/link` for all internal navigation — never `<a href>`

## API Route handlers
```typescript
// app/api/approvals/[id]/route.ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from "next/server"
import { db } from "@/lib/db"
import { z } from "zod"

const ApprovalBody = z.object({ decision: z.enum(["approve", "reject"]) })

export async function POST(req: NextRequest, { params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  const body = ApprovalBody.safeParse(await req.json())
  if (!body.success) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Invalid body" }, { status: 400 })

  const action = await db.pendingAction.findUnique({ where: { id: params.id } })
  if (!action) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Not found" }, { status: 404 })
  if (action.expiresAt < new Date()) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Expired" }, { status: 410 })

  // process...
  return NextResponse.json({ status: "ok" })
}
```

## Chat interface (Claude Code style)
- Model: `claude-sonnet-4-20250514` via Anthropic API with streaming
- Use Vercel AI SDK (`ai` package) for streaming responses
- Always inject fresh business context at session start (P&L summary, active signals, top campaigns)
- Show tool call traces inline in the chat — when Claude queries ClickHouse, show the query
- Tool call display component: `<ToolCallTrace tool="clickhouse_query" input={...} result={...} />`
- Chat history stored in React state only — not persisted (session-scoped like Claude Code)
- Slash commands: parse `/pnl`, `/campaigns`, `/signals`, `/explain {signal_id}` client-side before sending to API

## Metrics and charts
- All chart data fetched server-side via Cube REST API (through `/api/metrics/*` routes)
- Use `recharts` for all charts — consistent library, no mixing
- Always show loading skeleton while data fetches (use `loading.tsx` files in App Router)
- MetricCard component shows: label, value, delta (WoW), trend arrow — always round to 2 decimal places
- Currency: use `Intl.NumberFormat` with `style: "currency"` — never manual `$` prefix
- Percentages: always `(value * 100).toFixed(1) + "%"` — never raw decimals

## Approval queue UI rules
- Each action card must show in order: agent name → signal that triggered it → proposed action → expected outcome → risk badge
- Risk badge colors: low = green, medium = amber, high = red
- Approve/Reject buttons always require a confirmation step — no single-click irreversible actions
- Show expiry countdown on each pending action
- After approval/rejection: optimistic UI update immediately, revalidate from server

## Environment variables (frontend)
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=         # Orchestrator API base URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=          # WebSocket server URL
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=           # Server-side only — for chat API route
DATABASE_URL=                # Server-side only
REDIS_URL=                   # Server-side only
CUBE_API_URL=                # Cube REST endpoint
CUBE_API_TOKEN=              # Cube auth token
```
Never expose `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `DATABASE_URL`, or `REDIS_URL` to the client — no `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix on these.

## Tailwind conventions
- Dark mode: use `dark:` variants — the app supports both light and dark
- Spacing: multiples of 4px (1=4px, 2=8px, 4=16px, 6=24px, 8=32px)
- Colors: map to the semantic layer (slate for UI chrome, blue for info, green for success, amber for warning, red for danger)
- Never use arbitrary values like `w-[347px]` — use the closest Tailwind scale value
- Component variants: use `class-variance-authority (cva)` for multi-variant components
